## Diagram 5: Denormalization Trade-Off

```mermaid
graph TB
    A["SearchRecord in MongoDB"]
    
    A --> B["Denormalized (Same Data Stored Multiple Times)"]
    
    B --> C["Benefits ✅"]
    B --> D["Trade-Offs ⚠️"]
    
    C --> C1["Fast Search<br/>(No joins)"]
    C --> C2["Fast Display<br/>(transcript_names ready)"]
    C --> C3["All Data<br/>in One Document"]
    
    D --> D1["If Translator Changes<br/>Must Reindex"]
    D --> D2["Storage Overhead<br/>(Duplicate Data)"]
    D --> D3["Complex Updates<br/>(Update all copies)"]
    
    style A fill:#e1f5ff
    style B fill:#b3e5fc
    style C fill:#c8e6c9
    style D fill:#ffcdd2
    style C1 fill:#a5d6a7
    style C2 fill:#a5d6a7
    style C3 fill:#a5d6a7
    style D1 fill:#ef9a9a
    style D2 fill:#ef9a9a
    style D3 fill:#ef9a9a
```

